  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>Breakfast has always been the most important meal of the day and at the Montavis Lodge they strongly believe it. Treat yourself the the lodge's breakfast buffet which serves organic and fair trade food including, pastries, cereal, yoghurt, fruit, jams, cold cuts, cheese and even free range eggs which you can cook yourself at the table!</p>
<p>The breakfast room doubles up as the lounge and bar. Throughout the day the bar is open, so feel free to pop in for a cold beer or glass of wine.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <cateringShortDescription></cateringShortDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>1</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Montavis Lodge is in an excellent location, with a panoramic view of <a data-udi="umb://document/2924b00d292b448aab37c17b931cf845" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2924b00d292b448aab37c17b931cf845}" title="Livigno">Livigno</a>. It is perfect for you if your idea of happiness is having stunning hiking trails and adrenaline filled bike adventures right on your doorstep. It has a very relaxed atmosphere and has been decorated in a modern, minimalist and eco-friendly style; using only natural materials. The lodge style rooms are simple but cosy - they all have incredibly comfortable beds, so you're pretty much guaranteed a good nights sleep. </p>
<p>The hotel's team love the the local area and will go out of their way to make sure you experience it to its fullest- so feel free to chat to them for tips and tricks! The hotel is all about the activity holiday and has a weekly programme of free activities like hiking and mountain biking - hiring a guide to help you discover the beautiful local trails is a great idea for a family outing.</p>
<p>At the end of a long day, the bar area is very laid back and the perfect spot for relaxing with a beer and catching up with friends. Being on bed and breakfast means you can try out the local restaurants. Food is the best way to discover a new place, so we'd highly recommend asking the hotel for the best food spots. </p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 3 hours by coach from Innsbruck airport.</p>
<p>Throughout September: transfers will go through St. Moritz and take approx. 3.5 hours</p>]]></description>
